cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the fundamental limit of secure transmission over multi-user wireless communication systems, which is a core topic in information theory. 
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper focuses on the security aspect of the communication system by considering an external eavesdropper. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with wireless communication systems, which is a subfield of networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper models the communication system as a finite state MAC with delayed state feedback, which is a system and control problem. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper uses a degraded Gaussian fading example to illustrate the results, which is a common model in multimedia communication systems.
